tps://unpo.org/article/20231|title=UNPO: Assyria: Crowds Gather to Protest Mayor\u2019s Unfounded Expulsion|website=unpo.org|access-date=2019-07-15}}</ref> Zara argued that only Kurdistan Regional Government can keep the locals of [[Alqosh]] safe, mentioning the situation in [[Mosul]] as a reason to not trust the federal government in [[Baghdad]].<ref>{{cite news  |author=Wilson Face |title=Un irr\u00e9ductible village chr\u00e9tien en r\u00e9volte contre le Kurdistan  |url=https://www.lorientlejour.com/article/1074388/un-irreductible-village-chretien-en-revolte-contre-le-kurdistan-dictatorial-.html |accessdate=15 June 2019 |work=L'Orient-Le Jour |date=25 September 2017 |language=fr}}</ref> In April 2019, Zara welcomed a delegation from the [[United States]] led by Deputy Chief of the American embassy in Iraq and Consul General in Kurdistan Steve Fagan to Alqosh for the inspection of the Tomb of Prophet [[Nahum]] located in the town.<ref>{{cite news |title=\u0648\u0641\u062f \u0623\u0645\u0631\u064a\u0643\u064a \u0639\u0627\u0644 \u0627\u0644\u0645\u0633\u062a\u0648\u0649 \u064a\u0632\u0648\u0631 \u0628\u0644\u062f\u0629 \u0622\u0644\u0642\u0648\u0634 \u0627\u0644\u0623\u062b\u0631\u064a\u0629 \u0628\u0645\u0646\u0627\u0633\u0628\u0629 \u0639\u064a\u062f \u0627\u0644\u0642\u064a\u0627\u0645\u0629 |url=https://www.kurdistantv.net/ar/2019/04/23/kurdistan/%D9%88%D9%81%D8%AF-%D8%A3%D9%85%D8%B1%D9%8A%D9%83%D9%8A-%D8%B9%D8%A7%D9%84-%D8%A7%D9%84%D9%85%D8%B3%D8%AA%D9%88%D9%89-%D9%8A%D8%B2%D9%88%D8%B1-%D8%A8%D9%84%D8%AF%D8%A9-%D8%A2%D9%84%D9%82%D9%88%D8%B4-%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%A3%D8%AB%D8%B1%D9%8A%D8%A9-%D8%A8%D9%85%D9%86%D8%A7%D8%B3%D8%A8%D8%A9-%D8%B9%D9%8A%D8%AF-%D8%A7%D9%84%D9%82%D9%8A%D8%A7%D9%85%D8%A9 |accessdate=15 June 2019 |date=23 April 2019 |language=ar}}</ref> In June 2019, she visited America and met with American officials to raise awareness of the circumstances of the Christians in the country.<ref>{{cite news |title=Mayor of Al Qosh visits Washington to raise awareness of status of Christians in Iraq of Al Qosh visits Washington to raise awareness of status of Christians in Iraq - Representation in the United States |url=https://us.gov.krd/en/news-and-press-releases/mayor-of-al-qosh-visits-washington-to-raise-awareness-of-status-of-christians-in-iraq/ |accessdate=15 June 2019 |work=us.gov.krd |date=14 June 2019}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Zara, Lara}}\n[[Category:1982 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Chaldean Catholics]]\n[[Category:Iraqi women in politics]]\n[[Category:Iraqi Assyrian people]]\n[[Category:Kurdistan]]\n[[Category:People from Nineveh Governorate]]\n[[Category:Peshmerga]]\n[[Category:Kurdistan Democratic Party politicians]]\n", "name_user": "Ashurpedia", "label": "safe", "comment": "Deleted unreliable information. That article even says that Lara is the first Christian mayor in Iraq when there are multiple predecessors (Faiez Jahwareh for example) who are Christians.", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Lara_Zara"}
